            "answer_text": "The median full time salary, before tax, in London is \u00a339,476.  How an average salary in London compares to other big cities If you earn more than that, you are doing better than half the people around you. Is that good? That is a value judgement for you. It is worth noting that the distribution of incomes in London is huge, and there will be groups of people who are amazed that anyone can survive in London on less than \u00a360k, and would count any salary below \u00a3100k as poor. If you are considering moving to London from abroad you need to bear in mind that the median includes counting the salaries of many people who also receive public subsidies in the form of direct benefits or social housing, neither of which would be available to a foreign arrival in the city. ",
